    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="953"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Ap4/24</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British Embassy has the honour to inform the State Department that the
                    British Government reserves all rights under accepted principles and practice of
                    international law with regard to the <hi rend="italic">Appam</hi>, and that any
                    action taken in the matter by the owners in maintenance of their interests is
                    not in any way to be considered as prejudicing any claim advanced or to be
                    advanced by the British Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
